description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blood Production Assistant&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working in one or more of our laboratories, you’ll provide vital support to qualified scientific staff in a role that could involve anything from sample or reagent preparation to assisting with laboratory testing. You may also be relied on to update our donor and patient information and to generate computerised reports or worksheets should the need arise.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; This position demands great team working skills, meticulous attention to detail and the ability to precisely follow written instructions. Ideally, we would also like to see GCSEs at grades C or above in Maths and English or another equivalent qualification, such as an NVQ.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Blood and Transplant (NHSBT) offers a dynamic and friendly working environment where teamwork is highly valued. Personal development is also considered a priority and is supported through extensive training and development opportunities open to all employees.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working hours for the role will be 04:30am to 13:00pm Monday to Friday. You will be working as part of a team of 7.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This vacancy will close at 23:59 on Wednesday 11th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are invited to a selection day, we anticipate this will be taking place week commencing Monday 23rd November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have any enquiries regarding the vacancy, please contact barry.ainsworth@nhsbt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
